data.label: Role
data.description: A socially recognized status that carries a set of responsibilities, expectations, and norms established by a professional or social community. Role morality evaluates ethical behavior through the lens of such responsibilities, considering the professional context, standards, and historical precedents. Roles guide ethical judgment and competence both for humans and AI systems within their domain of application.
